item.title: Problem with [317]
item.dc:creator: @DivineSouls DivineSouls
item.description:
@DivineSouls wrote:

Ok, don’t worry this is a rather simple problem to fix - this is what my friend did -

I’m assuming you have a windows 7 64bit computer? Well if so, you need to uninstall your Java, and reinstall it with a 32bit version. You can do that by when you go to the site and download the JDK -

http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk6-jsp-136632.html

Click download - Than you are going to see a drop-down menu called “platforms” Instead of choosing windows 64x, you want to just choose “windows”. Download it - it should work now.

Read full topic
